---
/**
 * Goodyear Personal Injury Attorneys — Location Page
 * West Valley Core. I-10 corridor. 10,000 crashes 2018-2024. Road Safety Action Plan.
 */

import PracticeAreaLayout from '../layouts/PracticeAreaLayout.astro';
import { getLocalBusinessSchema } from '../utils/schema';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'How many crashes happen in Goodyear?',
    answer: 'Goodyear logged 10,000 traffic crashes on its roadways between 2018 and 2024. Of those, 59 were fatal and 170 resulted in serious injuries. The city is developing a Road Safety Action Plan for 2026 to address the trend.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What are the most dangerous roads in Goodyear?',
    answer: 'I-10 through Goodyear carries roughly 48% truck traffic. The Litchfield Road, Estrella Parkway, and Bullard Avenue interchanges with I-10 all show increasing crash frequency year over year in ADOT\'s data. Surface streets near Palm Valley, Estrella, and Canyon Trails developments see heavy residential traffic.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How long do I have to file a personal injury claim in Goodyear?',
    answer: 'Two years from the date of the crash under ARS 12-542. For wrongful death, two years from the date of death under ARS 12-611. Evidence degrades fast. Start early.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Do you have an office in Goodyear?',
    answer: 'Our headquarters is in Buckeye, right next door. Goodyear residents are typically 10 to 15 minutes from our office. We handle cases across the West Valley and know Goodyear\'s roads from firsthand experience.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What does it cost to hire an injury attorney?',
    answer: 'Nothing upfront. Contingency basis. You pay nothing unless we recover money for you.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Can I recover compensation if I was partially at fault?',
    answer: 'Yes. Arizona\'s pure comparative negligence rule under ARS 12-2505 means your recovery gets reduced by your fault percentage but doesn\'t disappear.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What about truck crashes on I-10 through Goodyear?',
    answer: 'I-10 through Goodyear carries some of the heaviest commercial truck traffic in Maricopa County. We handle truck crash cases and pull FMCSA carrier records, ELD data, and ADOT crash reports. Trucking company rapid-response teams arrive within hours. Your attorney needs to move fast.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What should I do after a crash in Goodyear?',
    answer: 'Call 911. Get medical attention within 24 hours. Document everything. Don\'t give a recorded statement to the other driver\'s insurance company. Call (602) 654-0202. The consultation is free.',
  },
];

const localSchema = getLocalBusinessSchema('Goodyear', 'goodyear');
---

<PracticeAreaLayout
  title="Goodyear Personal Injury Attorneys"
  description="Arizona injury cases, handled differently — serving Goodyear. 10,000 crashes in six years across I-10, Litchfield Rd and Estrella Pkwy. Call (602) 654-0202."
  canonical="/goodyear/"
  practiceArea="Goodyear Personal Injury Attorneys"
  heroTitle="Goodyear Personal Injury Lawyers"
  heroSubtitle="Ten minutes from our Buckeye HQ. We know the I-10 interchanges and the roads where Goodyear crashes concentrate. Contingency representation."
  heroImage="/images/heroes/goodyear.webp"
  faqs={faqs}
  schema={localSchema}
>
  <p>
    I drive through Goodyear every time I take I-10 between our Buckeye office and Phoenix. The Litchfield Road interchange. The Estrella Parkway exit. The Bullard Avenue merge. I know where traffic stacks up. I know where the speed differential between trucks and cars gets dangerous.
  </p>

  <p>
    Goodyear logged 10,000 traffic crashes on its roadways between 2018 and 2024. Fifty-nine fatal. 170 serious injuries. The city is developing a Road Safety Action Plan for 2026, collecting public input on which corridors need intervention. The data already tells the story.
  </p>

  <h2>I-10 Through Goodyear: The Freight Corridor</h2>

  <p>
    The I-10 corridor through Goodyear carries roughly 48 percent truck traffic between Loop 303 and Tonopah. Nearly half the vehicles on this stretch are commercial. Speed limits hit 65 mph inside Goodyear and jump to 75 west of Estrella Parkway. Trucks run at 65 across both zones.
  </p>

  <p>
    That speed differential is the problem. Passenger vehicles stack up behind semis and try to pass in tight windows. The closing speeds are unforgiving. I wrote a full investigation on the <a href="/investigations/i-10-crash-data-buckeye-goodyear/">I-10 crash data for Buckeye and Goodyear</a> with intersection-level breakdowns and ADOT's fatality rate analysis.
  </p>

  <p>
    The <a href="/investigations/truck-crashes-maricopa-county-data/">truck crash data for Maricopa County</a> shows 14,069 trucks involved in Arizona crashes in 2024. The <a href="/investigations/ghost-fleets-chameleon-carriers-i10/">chameleon carriers investigation</a> explains why some of those trucks have safety records that don't match their actual history.
  </p>

  <h2>Growth Without Infrastructure</h2>

  <p>
    Goodyear's population grew from roughly 95,000 in 2020 to over 115,000 in 2024. Palm Valley, Estrella, Canyon Trails, and PebbleCreek are all generating thousands of daily vehicle trips on roads that weren't designed for this volume.
  </p>

  <p>
    The I-10 and Bullard Avenue interchange, the I-10 and Litchfield Road interchange, and the I-10 and Dysart Road interchange all show increasing crash frequency year over year in ADOT's data. Walmart built a $152 million distribution facility near I-10 and Loop 101, adding more truck traffic to the mix.
  </p>

  <p>
    Goodyear faces the same infrastructure lag that's hitting Buckeye. New homes go up in 18 months. Road improvements take three to five years. Crashes happen in the gap.
  </p>

  <h2>Pedestrian Safety in the Suburbs</h2>

  <p>
    Arizona's pedestrian fatality rate is 3.6 per 100,000 residents, nearly twice the national average. The <a href="/investigations/arizona-pedestrian-deaths-road-design/">pedestrian deaths investigation</a> I published shows that 76 percent of pedestrian fatalities happen in darkness on wide arterials designed for vehicle speed, not pedestrian safety.
  </p>

  <p>
    Goodyear's arterials fit that profile. Wide lanes, high speed limits, residential developments feeding onto roads with no sidewalks or crosswalks. Evening hours are the deadliest. Arizona's summer heat pushes outdoor activity to the evening. Road conditions are most dangerous for people on foot at precisely that time.
  </p>

  <h2>Ten Minutes From Our Office</h2>

  <p>
    Our headquarters is in Buckeye. Goodyear residents are typically 10 to 15 minutes away. When I investigate a crash on Litchfield Road or at the Estrella Parkway interchange, I'm driving down the street, not across the Valley.
  </p>

  <p>
    Three people work your case. I investigate the scene and build the evidence. Brandon Millam handles the legal strategy. Stephanie Ramirez keeps you updated. That trio works the same way whether the crash happened on I-10, on a Goodyear surface street, or in a parking lot on Litchfield Road.
  </p>

  <p>
    If you or someone in your family was in a crash in Goodyear, call <a href="tel:+16026540202">(602) 654-0202</a> or use our contact form. The consultation is free. We don't charge unless we recover money for you.
  </p>
</PracticeAreaLayout>
